author: JerryRigEverything
description: I've had a pair of Channellock tongue and groove pliers in my tool box for a decade now and had NO IDEA the factory was so cool. Channel lock has been making these pliers in the USA for 140 years - and they finally allowed us inside to see how it all happens. THANK YOU CHANNELLOCK. Check them out here: https://www.channellock.com/
title: How to Make Pliers
